Product of Array Except Self
Solved
Medium
Topics
premium lock icon
Companies
Hint
Given an integer array nums, return an array answer such that answer[i] is equal to the product of all the elements of nums except nums[i].

The product of any prefix or suffix of nums is guaranteed to fit in a 32-bit integer.

You must write an algorithm that runs in O(n) time and without using the division operation.

 

Example 1:

Input: nums = [1,2,3,4]
Output: [24,12,8,6]
Example 2:

Input: nums = [-1,1,0,-3,3]
Output: [0,0,9,0,0]
 

Constraints:

2 <= nums.length <= 105
-30 <= nums[i] <= 30
The input is generated such that answer[i] is guaranteed to fit in a 32-bit integer.



Brute::

class Solution {
    public int[] productExceptSelf(int[] nums) {

    int [] arr = new int [nums.length];

    for(int i = 0;i<nums.length;i++){
        int prod = 1;
        for(int j = 0;j<nums.length;j++){
          
           if(i==j) {
            continue;
           }
           else{
            prod*=nums[j];
           }
           


        }
        arr[i] = prod;
    }
    

        return arr;
    }
}


Better::


Better Approach (Using Extra Left & Right Arrays)
ðŸ’¡ Idea

For every index i:

answer[i] = product of all left elements Ã— product of all right elements

Instead of recalculating every time, we precompute:

left[i] â†’ product of elements before i

right[i] â†’ product of elements after i

ðŸ”Ž Example
nums = [1,2,3,4]
Step 1: Build Left array
left[0] = 1
left[1] = 1
left[2] = 1Ã—2 = 2
left[3] = 1Ã—2Ã—3 = 6

left = [1,1,2,6]
Step 2: Build Right array
right[3] = 1
right[2] = 4
right[1] = 4Ã—3 = 12
right[0] = 4Ã—3Ã—2 = 24

right = [24,12,4,1]
Step 3: Multiply
result[i] = left[i] Ã— right[i]
 
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Try programiz.pro");
        
       int arr [] = {3,9,5,6,5};
       int left [] = new int [arr.length];
       int right [] = new int [arr.length];
       
        left[0] = 1;
       for(int i = 1;i<arr.length;i++){
         left[i] = left[i-1]*arr[i-1];
           
       }
        right[arr.length-1] = 1;
       
       for(int i = arr.length-2;i>=0;i--){
           right[i] = right[i+1]*arr[i+1];
           
       }
       int res [] = new int [arr.length];
       
       for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
           res[i] = left[i]*right[i];
           
       }
      
      System.out.println(Arrays.toString(res));
     
       
        
        
    }
}


Optimal::::



class Solution {
    public int[] productExceptSelf(int[] nums) {

       int left [] = new int [nums.length];

       
        left[0] = 1;

       for(int i = 1;i<nums.length;i++){
         left[i] = left[i-1]*nums[i-1];
           
         }

       int res [] = new int [nums.length];
       int right = 1;

       for(int i = nums.length-1;i>=0;i--){
           res[i] = left[i]*right;
           right = right*nums[i];
           
       }

        return res;
    }
}

